<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 20 at 7:47AM CDT  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Hancock, southeastern Henderson, southwestern Warren and northwestern
McDonough Counties through 830 AM CDT...
At 747 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Carthage, moving northeast at 60 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Carthage, La Harpe, Stronghurst, Blandinsville, Terre Haute, Ferris,
Raritan, Burnside, Disco, Fountain Green, Elvaston, Bentley,
Henderson County Fairgrounds, Webster and Decorra.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
